[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] The result, held in `inp`, is a list whose components are the three vectors read in.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] More conveniently, the dummy list can have named components, in which case the names can be used to access the vectors read in.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] or the list may be attached at position 2 of the search path (see Attaching arbitrary lists).
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] If the second argument is a single value and not a list, a single vector is read in, all components of which must be of the same mode as the dummy value.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] There are more elaborate input facilities available and these are detailed in the manuals.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] Around 100 datasets are supplied with R (in package **datasets**), and others are available in packages (including the recommended packages supplied with R).
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] All the datasets supplied with R are available directly by name.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] and this can still be used with the standard packages (as in this example).
