[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] If a package has been attached by `library`, its datasets are automatically included in the search.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] User-contributed packages can be a rich source of datasets.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] When invoked on a data frame or matrix, `edit` brings up a separate spreadsheet-like environment for editing.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] This is useful for making small changes once a data set has been read.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] will allow you to edit your data set `xold`, and on completion the changed object is assigned to `xnew`.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p02] If you want to alter the original dataset `xold`, the simplest way is to use `fix(xold)`, which is equivalent to `xold <- edit(xold)`.
