[src:r-language/r-intro-p06] The next section will look at data from the classical experiment of Michelson to measure the speed of light.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p06] This dataset is available in the `morley` object, but we will read it to illustrate the `read.table` function.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p06] Read in the Michelson data as a data frame, and look at it.
[src:r-language/r-intro-p06] There are five experiments (column `Expt`) and each has 20 runs (column `Run`) and `sl` is the recorded speed of light, suitably coded.
